{"name": "django-ical", "metadata": {"name": "django-ical", "version": "1.9.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Plugins", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django", "Framework :: Django :: 3.2", "Framework :: Django :: 4.0", "Framework :: Django :: 4.1", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": "https://github.com/jazzband/django-ical", "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["django", "icalendar", "django-recurrence"], "summary": "iCal feeds for Django based on Django's syndication feed framework.", "upload_time": 1686583357}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  build: |-\n    ```{image} https://github.com/jazzband/django-ical/workflows/Test/badge.svg\n    :alt: GitHub Actions\n    :target: https://github.com/jazzband/django-ical/actions\n    ```\n  coverage: |-\n    ```{image} https://codecov.io/gh/jazzband/django-ical/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n    :alt: Coverage\n    :target: https://codecov.io/gh/jazzband/django-ical\n    ```\n  docs: |-\n    ```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/django-ical/badge/?version=latest\n    :alt: Documentation Status\n    :scale: 100%\n    :target: http://django-ical.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest\n    ```\n  jazzband: |-\n    ```{image} https://jazzband.co/static/img/badge.svg\n    :alt: Jazzband\n    :target: https://jazzband.co/\n    ```\n  pypi: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/django-ical.svg\n    :alt: PyPI\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/django-ical/\n    ```\n---\n\n# django-ical\n\n{{ pypi }} {{ docs }} {{ build }} {{ coverage }} {{ jazzband }}\n\ndjango-ical is a simple library/framework for creating\n[iCal](http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2445.txt)\nfeeds based in Django's\n[syndication feed framework](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.0/ref/contrib/syndication/).\n\nThis documentation is modeled after the documentation for the syndication feed\nframework so you can think of it as a simple extension.\n\nIf you are familiar with the Django syndication feed framework you should be\nable to be able to use django-ical fairly quickly. It works the same way as\nthe Django syndication framework but adds a few extension properties to\nsupport iCalendar feeds.\n\ndjango-ical uses the [icalendar](http://pypi.python.org/pypi/icalendar/) library\nunder the hood to generate iCalendar feeds.\n\n## Documentation\n\nDocumentation is hosted on Read the Docs:\n\n<https://django-ical.readthedocs.io/en/latest/>\n\n# Changes\n\n## 1.9.2 (2023-06-12)\n\n- Support all properties specified in RFC 5545\n  [magicbrothers]\n\n## 1.9.1 (2023-05-01)\n\n- Fix multiple CATEGORIES and add tests\n  [mjfinney]\n\n## 1.9.0 (2023-04-04)\n\n- Support for iCalendar VTODO elements\n  [wetneb]\n\n## 1.8.4 (2023-04-02)\n\n- Fix content-type charset declarations.\n  [lchanouha]\n- Update test matrix.\n  Add Python 3.11 and Django 4.1 support.\n  Deprecate Python 3.7 support.\n  [aleksihakli]\n\n## 1.8.3 (2022-01-25)\n\n- Enable Python 3.10 and Django 4.0 support.\n  [aleksihakli]\n\n## 1.8.2 (2022-01-13)\n\n- Deprecate universal Python 2 wheels.\n  [aleksihakli]\n\n## 1.8.1 (2022-01-08)\n\n- Drop Python 3.6 support and add Python 3.10 support.\n  [aleksihakli]\n\n## 1.8.0 (2021-05-21)\n\n- Add `VALARM` support and documentation.\n  [malteger]\n\n## 1.7.3 (2021-05-03)\n\n- Fix calendar `Content-Type` headers.\n  Previous configuration included multiple comma separated values\n  in the header, which is incompatible with the HTTP header specification.\n  [aleksihakli]\n\n## 1.7.2 (2020-12-16)\n\n- Add support for Python 3.9. [aleksihakli]\n- Add support for Django 3.1. [aleksihakli]\n- Add tox QA with black and prospector. [aleksihakli]\n- Migrate from Travis to GitHub Actions. [aleksihakli]\n\n## 1.7.1 (2020-05-09)\n\n- Drop support for Django 1.11 LTS. [aleksihakli]\n- Fix string comparison in tests. [aleksihakli]\n\n## 1.7.0 (2019-10-09)\n\n- Add calendar MIME types for feeds. [xkill]\n- Add attendees for calendar events. [webaholik]\n\n## 1.6.2 (2019-08-30)\n\n- Language and documentation improvements.\n\n## 1.6.1 (2019-08-30)\n\n- Python 3.8 and PyPy support.\n\n## 1.6 (2019-08-27)\n\n- Drop support for old Python and Django versions.\n  This enables support for new Django versions\n  which do not have Python 2 compatibility shims.\n- Add continuous delivery via Jazzband.\n- Add SCM versioning via setuptools_scm.\n\n## 1.5 (2018-10-10)\n\n- Add support for Django 1.11. *Thanks, Martin B\u00e4chtold*\n- Drop support for Python 2.6. *Thanks, Martin B\u00e4chtold*\n- Add support for categories, rrule, exrule, rrdate, exdate. *Thanks, Armin Leuprecht*\n- Fix a documentation typo. *Thanks, Giorgos Logiotatidis*\n- Add documentation and testing around recurring events. *Thanks, Christian Ledermann*\n- Remove tests for Django versions < 1.8 *Thanks, Christian Ledermann*\n\n## 1.4 (2016-05-08)\n\n- Django up to 1.9 is supported.\n- Added new `ttl` parameter. *Thanks, Diaz-Gutierrez*\n- Added support for Python 3. *Thanks, Ben Lopatin*\n- Fixed LAST-MODIFIED support. *Thanks, Brad Bell*\n\n## 1.3 (2014-11-26)\n\n- Django up to 1.7 is supported.\n- Added a new `file_name` parameter. *Thanks, browniebroke*\n- Added support for the `ORGANIZER` field. *Thanks, browniebroke*\n\n## 1.2 (2012-12-12)\n\n- Removed support for Django 1.2. It should still work, but it's not supported.\n- We now require icalendar 3.1.\n- Added support for the `GEO` field. *Thanks, null_radix!*\n\n## 1.1 (2012-10-26)\n\n- Fixed issues running tests on Django 1.2 and Django 1.5.\n\n## 1.0 (2012-05-06)\n\n- Initial Release\n"], "modules": [{"name": "django_ical.views", "documentation": ["Views for generating ical feeds."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "django_ical.views.FEED_EXTRA_FIELDS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_ical.views.ICAL_EXTRA_FIELDS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed", "bases": ["Feed"], "methods": [{"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Copied from django.contrib.syndication.views.Feed\n\nSupports file_name as a dynamic attr."]}, {"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed._get_dynamic_attr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "default", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Copied from django.contrib.syndication.views.Feed (v1.7.1)"]}, {"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed.method", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed.feed_extra_kwargs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed.item_timestamp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed.item_extra_kwargs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "item", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed.feed_type", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed.link", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["iCalendar Feed\n\nExisting Django syndication feeds\n\n:title: X-WR-CALNAME\n:description: X-WR-CALDESC\n:item_guid: UID\n:item_title: SUMMARY\n:item_description: DESCRIPTION\n:item_link: URL\n:item_updateddate: LAST-MODIFIED\n\nExtension fields\n\n:method: METHOD\n:timezone: X-WR-TIMEZONE\n:item_class: CLASS\n:item_timestamp: DTSTAMP\n:item_created: CREATED\n:item_start_datetime: DTSTART\n:item_end_datetime: DTEND\n:item_transparency: TRANSP\n:item_attendee: ATTENDEE\n:item_valarm: VALARM"]}], "exports": [{"name": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed", "xref": {"fqname": "django_ical.views.ICalFeed", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "django_ical.utils", "documentation": ["Utility functions to build calendar rules."], "functions": [{"name": "django_ical.utils.build_rrule", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "count", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "interval", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bysecond", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "byminute", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "byhour", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "byweekno", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bymonthday", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "byyearday", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bymonth", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "until", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bysetpos", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "wkst", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "byday", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "freq", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Build rrule dictionary for vRecur class.\n\n```\nparam count\n\nint\n\nparam interval\n\nint\n\nparam bysecond\n\nint\n\nparam byminute\n\nint\n\nparam byhour\n\nint\n\nparam byweekno\n\nint\n\nparam bymonthday\n\nint\n\nparam byyearday\n\nint\n\nparam bymonth\n\nint\n\nparam until\n\ndatetime\n\nparam bysetpos\n\nint\n\nparam wkst\n\nstr, two-letter weekday\n\nparam byday\n\nweekday\n\nparam freq\n\nstr, frequency name ('WEEK', 'MONTH', etc)\n\nreturn\n\ndict\n```\n"]}, {"name": "django_ical.utils.build_rrule_from_text", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rrule_str", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Build an rrule from a serialzed RRULE string."]}, {"name": "django_ical.utils.build_rrule_from_recurrences_rrule", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rule", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Build rrule dictionary for vRecur class from a django_recurrences rrule.\n\ndjango_recurrences is a popular implementation for recurrences in django.\nhttps://pypi.org/project/django-recurrence/\nthis is a shortcut to interface between recurrences and icalendar."]}, {"name": "django_ical.utils.build_rrule_from_dateutil_rrule", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rule", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Build rrule dictionary for vRecur class from a dateutil rrule.\n\nDateutils rrule is a popular implementation of rrule in python.\nhttps://pypi.org/project/python-dateutil/\nthis is a shortcut to interface between dateutil and icalendar."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_ical.tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_ical", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator", "documentation": ["iCalendar feed generation library -- used for generating\niCalendar feeds.\n\nSample usage:\n\n```pycon\n>>> from django_ical import feedgenerator\n>>> from datetime import datetime\n>>> feed = feedgenerator.ICal20Feed(\n...     title=\"My Events\",\n...     link=\"http://www.example.com/events.ical\",\n...     description=\"A iCalendar feed of my events.\",\n...     language=\"en\",\n... )\n>>> feed.add_item(\n...     title=\"Hello\",\n...     link=\"http://www.example.com/test/\",\n...     description=\"Testing.\",\n...     start_datetime=datetime(2012, 5, 6, 10, 00),\n...     end_datetime=datetime(2012, 5, 6, 12, 00),\n... )\n>>> fp = open('test.ical', 'wb')\n>>> feed.write(fp, 'utf-8')\n>>> fp.close()\n```\n\nFor definitions of the iCalendar format see:\n<http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2445.txt>\n"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator.FEED_FIELD_MAP", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator.ITEM_ELEMENT_FIELD_MAP", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator.DefaultFeed", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator.ICal20Feed", "bases": ["SyndicationFeed"], "methods": [{"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator.ICal20Feed.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "outfile", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "encoding", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Writes the feed to the specified file in the\nspecified encoding."]}, {"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator.ICal20Feed.write_items", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "calendar", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Write all elements to the calendar"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "django_ical.feedgenerator.ICal20Feed.mime_type", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variab